INSERT INTO `recipe` VALUES (11,'2023-09-08 07:27:33.973735',NULL,'In a mixing bowl, combine flour, eggs, milk, and a pinch of salt. Whisk until smooth. Let it rest for 30 minutes.\nCook the Pancakes:\n\nHeat a non-stick skillet over medium heat and add a small amount of butter.\nPour a ladleful of pancake batter into the skillet, swirling it to cover the bottom.\nCook until the pancake is set and lightly browned on both sides. Repeat with the remaining batter.\nPrepare the Meat Filling:\n\nIn a separate pan, sauté the chopped onion and garlic until translucent.\nAdd ground beef and cook until browned.\nSeason with paprika, salt, and pepper. Set aside.\nFill the Pancakes:\n\nPlace a few spoonfuls of the meat filling onto each pancake.\nRoll up the pancakes, tucking in the sides, to form a neat package.\nMake the Sauce:\n\nIn a saucepan, combine beef broth, sour cream, flour, and paprika. Whisk until smooth.\nCook over low heat, stirring constantly, until the sauce thickens.\nSeason with salt and pepper.\nServe:\n\nPour the sauce over the stuffed pancakes.\nOptionally, garnish with more sour cream and chopped parsley.\nEnjoy your Hortobágyi húsos palacsinta!','2023-09-22 07:14:46.390542','Meat Pancakes',5,2,'cheap','easy',80,'aka \"Hortobágyi palacsinta\"',0),(12,'2023-09-08 07:39:45.404544',NULL,'Place the grated zucchinis in a clean kitchen towel or cheesecloth and squeeze out excess moisture. This will help prevent the fritters from being too watery.\nMix the Vegetables:\n\nIn a large mixing bowl, combine the grated zucchini, grated carrot, chopped red bell pepper, corn kernels, green onions, and chopped parsley.\nPrepare the Batter:\n\nIn a separate bowl, mix the chickpea flour, nutritional yeast (if using), garlic powder, onion powder, paprika, salt, and pepper.\nGradually add water to the dry ingredients, stirring until you have a smooth batter. The batter should be thick enough to coat the back of a spoon.\nCombine and Mix:\n\nPour the batter over the grated vegetables and mix until everything is well combined.\nFry the Fritters:\n\nHeat a skillet or frying pan over medium-high heat and add a tablespoon of vegetable oil.\nScoop a spoonful of the vegetable mixture and drop it onto the hot skillet, flattening it slightly with the back of the spoon.\nCook until the fritters are golden brown on one side (about 3-4 minutes), then flip and cook the other side until it\'s also golden brown.\nContinue this process until all the fritters are cooked, adding more oil to the pan as needed.\nServe:\n\nTransfer the cooked fritters to a plate lined with paper towels to remove excess oil.\nServe the vegan zucchini vegetable fritters hot, with your favorite dipping sauce or vegan yogurt.\n\nEnjoy your delicious vegan Zucchini Vegetable Fritters!','2023-09-15 07:36:50.418542','Zucchini Fritters',7,6,'medium','medium',65,'A Flavorful Delight',0),(13,'2023-09-08 08:06:37.196745',NULL,'In a mixing bowl, whip the cream until it forms stiff peaks.\nGently fold in the powdered sugar and vanilla extract. Set aside.\n\n2. Assemble the Cake:\n\nLine the sides of a round springform pan with strips of parchment paper, allowing them to extend above the rim of the pan.\nPlace a layer of sponge cake at the bottom of the pan.\nSpread half of the whipped cream mixture over the cake.\nLayer fresh berries on top of the cream.\nSpread a layer of raspberry jam over the berries.\nAdd another layer of sponge cake on top.\nRepeat the layers with the remaining whipped cream, berries, and jam.\nFinish with a layer of sponge cake on top.\n\n3. Chill:\n\nRefrigerate the cake for at least 4 hours or overnight to allow the flavors to meld.\n\n4. Prepare the Chocolate Ganache:\n\nIn a microwave-safe bowl, heat the heavy cream until it\'s hot but not boiling.\nPour the hot cream over the chocolate chips and let it sit for a minute.\nStir until smooth to create a glossy ganache.\n\n5. Decorate the Cake:\n\nCarefully remove the cake from the springform pan.\nPour the chocolate ganache over the top of the cake, allowing it to drip down the sides.\nDecorate with fresh berries, chocolate shavings, mint leaves, and a dusting of powdered sugar.\n\n6. Slice and Serve:\n\nSlice the Charlotte Royal Cake into portions and serve. Enjoy!','2023-09-21 15:43:52.525981','Charlotte Cake',4,3,'expensive','hard',150,'The Royal Elegance',0),(14,'2023-09-08 08:23:09.701561',NULL,'Preheat the oven to 400°F (200°C). Place the beef bones, onion, and ginger on a baking sheet and roast for about 30-40 minutes or until they become browned and fragrant.\nIn a large pot, add the roasted beef bones, onion, ginger, star anise, cloves, cinnamon sticks, black cardamom (if using), coriander seeds, and fennel seeds. Fill the pot with water to cover everything.\nBring to a boil and skim off any impurities that rise to the surface.\nReduce the heat to low, add salt, sugar, and fish sauce. Simmer uncovered for at least 4 hours (the longer, the better). Add water as needed to maintain the liquid level.\nStrain the broth through a fine-mesh strainer, discarding the solids. Keep the clear broth warm.\n\nSoak the rice noodles in hot water for about 20-30 minutes or until they are pliable. Drain and set aside.\nThinly slice the beef and set aside.\nPrepare the bean sprouts, Thai basil, cilantro, green onions, lime wedges, hoisin sauce, and sriracha for serving.\n\nIn serving bowls, place a portion of cooked rice noodles and thinly sliced beef.\nPour the hot broth over the noodles and beef. The hot broth will cook the beef slices.\nServe with bean sprouts, Thai basil, cilantro, green onions, lime wedges, hoisin sauce, and sriracha on the side.\n\nCustomize your Pho Bo with your preferred herbs and condiments. Squeeze lime, add fresh herbs, and drizzle sauces as desired. Mix and savor the rich flavors of this classic Vietnamese dish.','2023-09-08 08:23:09.701561','Pho Bo',3,1,'medium','medium',720,'Where Flavor meets Tradition',0),(15,'2023-09-08 09:00:07.978794',NULL,'Preheat your oven to 400°F (200°C).\nPlace the trimmed asparagus spears on a baking sheet, drizzle with olive oil, and season with salt and pepper.\nToss to coat the asparagus evenly and spread them out in a single layer.\nRoast in the oven for about 10-15 minutes or until the asparagus is tender but still crisp.\n\nMake the Hollandaise Sauce:\n\nIn a heatproof bowl, whisk together the egg yolks and lemon juice until well combined.\nPlace the bowl over a pot of simmering water (double boiler) without allowing the bottom of the bowl to touch the water.\nSlowly drizzle in the melted butter while continuously whisking the egg yolk mixture. Continue whisking until the sauce thickens and emulsifies.\nRemove the bowl from heat and season the hollandaise sauce with cayenne pepper, salt, and pepper. Keep it warm.\n\nServe:\n\nArrange the roasted asparagus on a serving platter.\nDrizzle the warm hollandaise sauce over the asparagus.\nGarnish with chopped fresh parsley, if desired.\n\nServe your Asparagus with Hollandaise Sauce as a delicious side dish that pairs perfectly with a variety of main courses.','2023-09-08 09:26:50.162828','Green Asparagus',8,18,'medium','easy',45,'à la Sauce Hollandaise',0),(16,'2023-09-08 09:20:22.663940',NULL,'If using dried chickpeas, soak them in water overnight or for at least 6 hours. Drain before using.\nIf using canned chickpeas, drain and rinse them well.\n\n2. Make the Falafel Mixture:\n\nIn a food processor, combine the chickpeas, chopped parsley, chopped cilantro, chopped onion, minced garlic, ground cumin, ground coriander, cayenne pepper, salt, and pepper.\nPulse until the mixture is well combined but still has some texture. Scrape down the sides of the processor as needed.\n\n3. Form the Falafel Patties:\n\nSprinkle in the baking powder and 1 tablespoon of flour. Pulse until the mixture resembles coarse meal. If it\'s too loose, add more flour as needed.\nShape the mixture into small patties, about the size of golf balls. You can use your hands or a falafel scoop for consistency.\n\n4. Fry the Falafel:\n\nHeat vegetable oil in a deep frying pan or pot to 350°F (175°C).\nCarefully slide the falafel patties into the hot oil using a slotted spoon. Fry in batches for about 3-4 minutes or until they are golden brown and crispy.\nRemove the falafel from the oil and place them on a plate lined with paper towels to drain excess oil.\n\n5. Serve:\n\nWarm the pita bread or flatbreads.\nStuff the bread with falafel patties, hummus, tzatziki or tahini sauce, fresh veggies, pickles, and sliced red onions.\nSqueeze fresh lemon juice over the top.\n\n6. Enjoy:\n\nFalafel is best served immediately while warm and crispy. Enjoy this delightful Middle Eastern treat!','2023-09-15 07:37:23.177408','Falafel',7,1,'medium','medium',55,'Street Food at Its Finest',0),(17,'2023-09-08 09:52:22.189071',NULL,'Season the chicken breasts with salt, black pepper, and Italian seasoning (if using).\nIn a skillet, heat olive oil over medium-high heat. Add the chicken breasts and cook for about 6-8 minutes per side or until cooked through and no longer pink in the center.\nRemove the chicken from the skillet, let it rest for a few minutes, and then slice it into thin strips.\n\nIn the same skillet, melt the butter over medium heat. Add minced garlic and cook for about 1 minute or until fragrant.\nPour in the heavy cream, stirring continuously until the mixture is heated through but not boiling.\nReduce the heat to low and gradually add the grated Parmesan cheese, stirring until the sauce is smooth and thickened.\nSeason the sauce with salt, white pepper, and ground nutmeg (if using).\n\nMeanwhile, cook the pasta according to the package instructions until al dente. Drain.\n\nToss the cooked pasta with the Alfredo sauce until well coated.\nArrange the sliced chicken on top.\nGarnish with chopped fresh parsley and grated Parmesan cheese.\n\nChicken Alfredo is best served hot, offering a creamy, cheesy, and satisfying meal.','2023-09-08 09:52:22.189071','Chicken Alfredo',2,6,'medium','medium',55,'A Creamy Italian Classic',0),(18,'2023-09-08 10:01:56.058944',NULL,'In a large skillet, brown the ground beef or Italian sausage over medium-high heat. Drain any excess fat.\nAdd chopped onion and minced garlic. Cook until the onion is soft and translucent.\nStir in crushed tomatoes, tomato paste, water, sugar, dried basil, salt, and black pepper. Simmer for 15-20 minutes, stirring occasionally.\n\nIn a bowl, combine ricotta cheese, grated Parmesan cheese, egg, chopped parsley, salt, and pepper. Mix until well combined.\n\nPreheat your oven to 375°F (190°C).\nSpread a thin layer of meat sauce in the bottom of a 9x13-inch baking dish.\nPlace 4 lasagne noodles on top of the sauce.\nSpread half of the ricotta mixture over the noodles.\nSprinkle 1 cup of mozzarella cheese on top.\nRepeat the layers: meat sauce, noodles, ricotta mixture, mozzarella cheese.\nFinish with a layer of meat sauce and the remaining mozzarella cheese.\n\nCover the baking dish with aluminum foil and bake for 25 minutes.\nRemove the foil and bake for an additional 25-30 minutes or until the lasagne is bubbly and the cheese is golden brown.\nAllow it to cool for a few minutes before slicing.\n\nLasagne is a comforting classic that tastes even better as leftovers the next day!','2023-09-08 10:02:34.612578','Lasagne',2,1,'medium','medium',45,'Italian Comfort for Your Soul',0),(19,'2023-09-08 10:13:40.682458',NULL,'In a saucepan, combine the halved strawberries, granulated sugar, fresh orange juice, lemon zest, and water.\nBring the mixture to a boil over medium-high heat. Reduce the heat and simmer for about 15 minutes, stirring occasionally, until the strawberries are soft and the liquid thickens.\nRemove from heat, let it cool slightly, and then blend until smooth using an immersion blender or regular blender.\nStir in the vanilla extract and chill in the refrigerator for at least 2 hours.\n\nIn another saucepan, combine cooked white rice, milk, granulated sugar, vanilla extract, and a pinch of salt.\nCook over medium heat, stirring frequently, until the mixture thickens and the rice becomes creamy. This will take about 15-20 minutes.\n\nTo serve, ladle the chilled strawberry soup into bowls.\nTop each bowl with a spoonful of rice cream.\nGarnish with fresh strawberry slices and mint leaves.\nOptionally, add a dollop of whipped cream for extra indulgence.\n\nStrawberry Soup with Rice Cream is a delightful and refreshing dessert, perfect for warm days or any occasion!','2023-09-08 10:13:40.682458','Strawberry Soup',3,18,'medium','easy',135,'A Summery Sweet Symphony',0),(20,'2023-09-08 10:26:11.703688',NULL,'In a shallow bowl, combine the breadcrumbs, grated Parmesan cheese, garlic powder, paprika, salt, and pepper.\nSet up a breading station with one bowl of flour, one bowl of beaten eggs, and one bowl of the breadcrumb mixture.\nDip each chicken piece into the flour, then the beaten eggs, and finally, coat them in the breadcrumb mixture, pressing the breadcrumbs onto the chicken to adhere.\n\nHeat cooking oil in a frying pan or deep fryer to 350°F (175°C).\nCarefully add the coated chicken pieces to the hot oil, a few at a time, making sure not to overcrowd the pan.\nFry the nuggets for about 3-4 minutes per side or until they are golden brown and crispy.\nUse a slotted spoon to remove the nuggets from the oil and place them on a plate lined with paper towels to drain any excess oil.\n\nArrange the crispy chicken nuggets on a serving platter.\nServe with your favorite dipping sauce on the side.\n\nChicken Nuggets are a beloved snack or meal for all ages. Perfect for kids and kids at heart!','2023-09-14 19:21:02.663235','Chicken Nuggets',5,2,'cheap','easy',60,'Happiness in Every Bite',0),(21,'2023-09-08 10:47:48.921011',NULL,'In a bowl, whisk together mayonnaise, minced garlic, lemon juice, Dijon mustard, Worcestershire sauce, grated Parmesan cheese, salt, and black pepper.\nSlowly drizzle in the olive oil while continuing to whisk until the dressing is well combined and creamy. Set aside.\n\nIn a large salad bowl, add the chopped romaine lettuce.\nDrizzle Caesar dressing over the lettuce, starting with a few tablespoons and adding more to taste.\nToss the lettuce in the dressing until it\'s evenly coated.\nAdd croutons and grated Parmesan cheese.\nGive the salad another gentle toss.\n\nDivide the Caesar Salad onto individual plates.\nFinish with a sprinkle of freshly ground black pepper.\n\nCaesar Salad is a classic that\'s both crisp and creamy, making it a favorite for salad lovers everywhere.','2023-09-08 10:47:48.921011','Caesar Salad',7,6,'cheap','easy',30,'A Timeless Classic',0),(22,'2023-09-08 10:57:24.908545',NULL,'Preheat Your Oven: Preheat your oven to its highest temperature (usually around 475-500°F or 245-260°C). If you have a pizza stone, place it in the oven while it preheats.\n\nPrepare the Dough: Roll out the pizza dough on a lightly floured surface into your desired thickness. You can make it round or rectangular, depending on your preference.\n\nAssemble the Pizza: Transfer the rolled-out dough to a pizza peel or a baking sheet lined with parchment paper. If you\'re using minced garlic, spread it evenly over the dough.\n\nAdd Sauce: Spread the tomato sauce evenly over the dough, leaving a small border around the edges for the crust.\n\nAdd Cheese: Sprinkle the mozzarella cheese evenly over the sauce.\n\nBake: If you\'re using a pizza stone, carefully slide the pizza onto the hot stone in the preheated oven. If you\'re using a baking sheet, simply place the sheet in the oven. Bake for about 10-12 minutes or until the crust is golden and the cheese is bubbly and slightly browned.\n\nFinish with Fresh Basil: Remove the pizza from the oven and immediately scatter fresh basil leaves over the hot, melted cheese.\n\nSeason and Serve: Drizzle a bit of olive oil over the top, season with salt and pepper to taste, and let it cool for a minute or two. Then slice and serve your delicious Margherita pizza!\n\nEnjoy your homemade Margherita pizza!','2023-09-14 12:52:48.762197','Margherita pizza',2,3,'cheap','easy',60,'Just Great!',0),(24,'2023-09-08 12:10:05.527883',NULL,'In a large mixing bowl, whisk together the flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, and salt.\n\nIn a separate bowl, whisk together the milk, egg, and melted butter.\n\nPour the wet ingredients into the dry ingredients and stir until just combined. It\'s okay if there are a few lumps. If you overmix, the pancakes may become tough.\n\nIf you\'re adding any optional ingredients like chocolate chips, blueberries, or nuts, fold them into the batter gently.\n\nPreheat a griddle or non-stick skillet over medium heat. Add a small amount of butter or oil and spread it around to coat the surface.\n\nUsing a 1/4-cup measuring cup, pour the batter onto the griddle/skillet for each pancake. Use the back of the measuring cup to spread the batter into a circle if needed.\n\nCook until you see bubbles forming on the surface of the pancakes, then flip them with a spatula. Cook for an additional 1-2 minutes, or until golden brown.\n\nRemove the pancakes from the griddle/skillet and keep them warm. You can do this by placing them on a baking sheet in a warm oven (around 200°F or 93°C).\n\nRepeat the process with the remaining batter, adding more butter or oil to the griddle/skillet as needed.\n\nServe the pancakes warm with your choice of toppings, such as maple syrup, fresh fruit, whipped cream, or a dusting of powdered sugar.\n\nEnjoy your delicious American pancakes!','2023-09-22 10:23:00.000000','Fluffy Pancake',4,2,'cheap','easy',30,'The Classic Breakfast',0),(25,'2023-09-14 19:56:58.495974',NULL,'1. Sauté the Aromatics:\nIn a large pot, heat the olive oil over medium heat. Add the chopped onion and garlic and sauté until they become fragrant and translucent.\n\n2. Cook the Pumpkin:\nAdd the diced pumpkin to the pot and stir to combine with the onions and garlic.\nPour in the vegetable or chicken broth until the pumpkin is mostly covered.\nAdd ground cinnamon, ground nutmeg, salt, and black pepper to the pot.\nBring the mixture to a boil, then reduce the heat to a simmer. Cover and cook for about 20-25 minutes, or until the pumpkin is tender and can be easily pierced with a fork.\n\n3. Blend the Soup:\nUse an immersion blender to puree the soup until smooth. Alternatively, transfer the soup in batches to a blender and blend until smooth. Be cautious when blending hot liquids.\n\n4. Add Cream and Adjust Seasoning:\nReturn the blended soup to the pot and stir in the heavy cream or coconut milk.\nTaste the soup and adjust the seasoning as needed with more salt, pepper, cinnamon, or nutmeg.\n\n5. Serve:\nLadle the pumpkin soup into bowls.\nGarnish with pumpkin seeds and fresh parsley if desired.\n\n6. Enjoy:\nPumpkin Soup is a comforting, creamy delight that\'s perfect for fall and winter meals.','2023-09-21 15:01:24.232000','Pumpkin Soup',3,18,'cheap','easy',90,'A Creamy Bowl of Autumn',0),(26,'2023-09-14 20:45:05.318523',NULL,'Prepare the Chicken:\n\nPreheat your oven to 375°F (190°C).\n\nMake a Pocket in the Chicken:\nLay each chicken breast flat on a cutting board.\nUse a sharp knife to cut a pocket into the side of each chicken breast. Be careful not to cut all the way through.\n\nSeason the Chicken:\nSeason the outside of the chicken breasts with salt and black pepper.\n\nPrepare the Spinach and Mushroom Stuffing:\nIn a skillet, heat olive oil over medium-high heat.\nAdd chopped mushrooms and cook until they release their moisture and turn golden brown.\nAdd chopped onion and minced garlic. Cook until the onion is soft and translucent.\nStir in chopped spinach and cook until it wilts.\nRemove the skillet from heat and mix in cream cheese and grated Parmesan cheese.\nSeason with salt and black pepper to taste.\n\nStuff the Chicken:\nCarefully stuff each chicken breast with the spinach and mushroom mixture.\nSecure the pockets with toothpicks to keep the filling inside.\n\nSear the Chicken:\nIn an oven-safe skillet, heat a bit more olive oil over medium-high heat.\nSear the stuffed chicken breasts for about 2-3 minutes per side or until they are golden brown.\n\nBake the Chicken:\nTransfer the skillet to the preheated oven and bake for about 20-25 minutes or until the chicken reaches an internal temperature of 165°F (74°C) and is no longer pink in the center.\n\nPrepare the Cream Sauce:\nIn a saucepan, combine heavy cream and chicken broth. Heat over medium heat until it starts to simmer.\nStir in grated Parmesan cheese and cook until the sauce thickens.\nSeason with salt and black pepper to taste.\n\nServe:\nRemove the toothpicks from the chicken.\nPour the creamy sauce over the stuffed chicken breasts.\nGarnish with chopped fresh parsley.\n\nEnjoy:\nCreamy Spinach and Mushroom Stuffed Chicken is an elegant and delicious dish that\'s perfect for special occasions or a delightful weeknight dinner.','2023-09-14 20:45:05.318523','Spinach Stuffed Chicken',5,6,'medium','medium',35,'A Weeknight Comfort',0),(27,'2023-09-15 09:02:31.915171',NULL,'1. Assemble the Skewers:\n\nTake a wooden skewer and slide on a cherry tomato, a fresh mozzarella ball, and a fresh basil leaf.\nRepeat this process for the desired number of skewers.\n\n2. Drizzle with Balsamic Glaze:\nArrange the assembled skewers on a serving platter.\nDrizzle with balsamic glaze just before serving.\n\n3. Serve:\nCaprese Salad Skewers are ready to impress your guests.','2023-09-20 12:49:25.329500','Caprese Salad Skewers',7,3,'medium','easy',15,'Pure Joy on a Stick',0),(28,'2023-09-15 10:37:13.679313','2023-09-24 08:23:04.000000','Preheat the Oven: Preheat your oven to 325°F (160°C).\n\nPrepare the Ham: Place the ham in a large roasting pan, fat side up. If the ham has a thick layer of fat, you can score it with a sharp knife in a criss-cross pattern to allow the glaze to penetrate.\n\nPrepare the Glaze:\n\nIn a medium saucepan, combine the brown sugar, Dijon mustard, apple cider vinegar, honey, ground cloves, and ground cinnamon.\nHeat over medium heat, stirring constantly, until the mixture is well combined and the sugar is completely dissolved.\nApply the Glaze:\n\nBrush a generous amount of the glaze over the surface of the ham using a basting brush. Make sure to coat it evenly.\nBake the Ham:\n\nPlace the ham in the preheated oven and bake for about 2.5 to 3 hours, or until the internal temperature reaches 140°F (60°C). This should be about 15-18 minutes per pound.\nBaste the Ham:\n\nEvery 30 minutes or so, take the ham out of the oven and baste it with more of the glaze to keep it moist and flavorful.\nLet it Rest:\n\nOnce the ham reaches the desired temperature, remove it from the oven and let it rest for about 15 minutes before carving.','2023-09-21 15:49:11.226395','Easter ham',5,1,'medium','hard',60,'You wont regret it!',0),(29,'2023-09-15 10:52:38.809701','2023-09-24 08:23:11.000000','Prepare the Meat:\n\nIf using pork, trim excess fat and cut into chunks. If using chicken thighs, leave them whole.\nIn a food processor, combine the meat, onion, garlic, oregano, thyme, cumin, paprika, salt, and pepper. Process until the mixture becomes a smooth paste.\nShape and Cook the Meat:\n\nPreheat your oven to 325°F (160°C).\nShape the meat mixture into a loaf shape or press it onto a skewer.\nIf you have a rotisserie, you can use that. Otherwise, you can place the meat on a rack in a baking dish.\nCook and Slice:\n\nRoast the meat in the preheated oven for about 1.5 to 2 hours, or until the internal temperature reaches 165°F (74°C).\nIf using a rotisserie, follow the manufacturer\'s instructions for cooking time.\nPrepare the Tzatziki:\n\nIn a bowl, combine yogurt, grated cucumber (squeeze out excess water), minced garlic, chopped dill, and a squeeze of lemon juice. Mix well and season with salt and pepper to taste.\nAssemble the Gyros:\n\nOnce the meat is cooked, let it rest for a few minutes before slicing it thinly.\nWarm the pita bread in the oven or on a skillet.\nServe:\n\nFill each pita with slices of gyro meat, tomatoes, cucumbers, red onion, and a generous dollop of tzatziki sauce.','2023-09-21 15:51:56.567465','Greek gyros',5,2,'medium','hard',80,'You wont regret it!',0),(32,'2023-09-20 07:23:45.413058',NULL,'1. Sauté Aromatics:\nHeat vegetable oil in a large skillet over medium heat.\nAdd finely chopped onion, minced garlic, and grated ginger.\nSauté until the onion is soft and translucent.\n\n2. Spice It Up:\nStir in curry powder, cumin, turmeric, and paprika.\nCook for another 2 minutes, stirring constantly to toast the spices.\n\n3. Add Chickpeas and Tomatoes:\nAdd the drained chickpeas and diced tomatoes to the skillet.\nStir well to combine.\n\n4. Simmer and Flavor:\nPour in the coconut milk, and season with salt and pepper.\nStir everything together and let it simmer for about 15-20 minutes, or until the sauce thickens slightly.\n\n5. Serve:\nServe your Vegan Chickpea Curry hot, garnished with fresh cilantro leaves.\nIt’s delicious on its own or over cooked rice or with naan bread.\n','2023-09-20 07:28:42.159152','Vegan Chickpea Curry',7,3,'cheap','medium',30,'A Flavor-Packed Plant-Powered Delight',0),(33,'2023-09-20 08:08:02.606083',NULL,'1. Sauté Aromatics:\nHeat olive oil in a large saucepan over medium heat.\nAdd finely chopped onion and minced garlic.\nSauté until the onion is soft and translucent.\n\n2. Simmer Tomatoes:\nPour in the crushed tomatoes.\nStir in chopped basil, dried oregano, sugar, and a pinch of red pepper flakes if you like a little heat.\nSeason with salt and pepper to taste.\n\n3. Simmer and Blend:\nReduce heat to low and let the sauce simmer for about 20-25 minutes, stirring occasionally.\nUse an immersion blender to blend the sauce until it reaches your desired smoothness.\n\n4. Serve:\nServe your Tomato Basil Pasta Sauce over your favorite cooked pasta.\nGarnish with fresh basil leaves and grated Parmesan cheese if desired.','2023-09-20 08:08:02.606083','Homemade Tomato Basil Pasta Sauce',2,1,'cheap','easy',30,'A Taste of Italy in Minutes',0),(34,'2023-09-20 08:20:45.770429',NULL,'1. Prepare the Teriyaki Sauce:\nIn a saucepan, combine soy sauce, mirin, sake, sugar, minced garlic, and grated ginger.\nBring to a simmer over medium heat, stirring until the sugar dissolves.\nReduce heat and simmer for 10-15 minutes or until the sauce thickens. Set aside.\n\n2. Prepar e the Chicken:\nSeason the chicken thighs with salt and pepper.\nHeat vegetable oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat.\nAdd chicken thighs and cook for about 5-6 minutes per side or until they are cooked through.\nBrush the cooked chicken with the prepared teriyaki sauce on both sides during the last 2 minutes of cooking.\n\n3. Slice and Serve:\nRemove the chicken from the skillet and let it rest for a few minutes.\nSlice the chicken into thin strips.\nServe the teriyaki chicken over steamed white rice, drizzle with more teriyaki sauce, and garnish with sesame seeds and sliced green onions if desired.','2023-09-20 08:22:06.809291','Japanese Teriyaki Chicken',11,6,'medium','medium',40,'A Sweet and Savory Japanese Delight',0),(35,'2023-09-20 08:29:13.318258',NULL,'1. Muddle the Mint:\nIn a glass, add the fresh mint leaves and sugar.\nGently muddle (crush) the mint leaves and sugar together to release their aroma and flavor.\n\n2. Add Lime Juice and Rum:\nPour in the fresh lime juice and white rum.\nStir well to combine.\n\n3. Add Crushed Ice:\nFill the glass with crushed ice, almost to the top.\n\n4. Top with Soda Water:\nTop off the glass with soda water (club soda), leaving some space at the top.\n\n5. Garnish:\nStir gently to mix the ingredients.\nGarnish with a lime wedge and a sprig of fresh mint.\n\n6. Serve and Enjoy:\nUse a straw or a long stirring stick to sip and enjoy your classic Mojito!','2023-09-21 15:56:09.473571','Classic Mojito',6,3,'medium','medium',10,'The Refreshing Cuban Cocktail',0),(36,'2023-09-20 08:44:19.001638',NULL,'1. Sear the Beef:\nIn a large pot, heat the vegetable oil over medium-high heat.\nAdd the cubed beef and brown on all sides. Remove and set aside.\n\n2. Sauté Onions and Garlic:\nIn the same pot, add chopped onions and minced garlic.\nSauté until the onions are soft and translucent.\n\n3. Add Paprika and Spices:\nStir in sweet paprika and caraway seeds (if using).\nAdd bay leaves and return the browned beef to the pot.\nMix well to coat the meat with the paprika.\n\n4. Simmer with Broth:\nPour in beef broth and bring to a boil.\nReduce heat to low, cover, and simmer for 1 hour or until the meat is tender.\n\n5. Add Vegetables:\nAdd diced potatoes, carrots, and red bell pepper to the pot.\nContinue to simmer for another 30 minutes or until the vegetables are cooked through.\n\n6. Season and Serve:\nSeason with salt and pepper to taste.\nServe your Hungarian Goulash hot, garnished with a dollop of sour cream (if desired) and chopped fresh parsley.','2023-09-20 08:44:19.001638','Hungarian Goulash',12,6,'medium','medium',120,'Bográcsgulyás – a hearty Hungarian classic',0),(39,'2023-09-20 09:08:55.946074',NULL,'1. Prepare the Lobsters:\nPreheat your oven to 400°F (200°C).\nUse a sharp knife to split the lobsters in half lengthwise.\nBrush them with olive oil, and season with salt and pepper.\nPlace the lobsters on a baking sheet, shell side up, and roast in the preheated oven for about 15-20 minutes, until the meat is opaque.\n\n2. Make the Thermidor Sauce:\nIn a saucepan, melt 4 tablespoons of unsalted butter over medium heat.\nAdd finely chopped shallots and minced garlic, and sauté until they are soft and translucent.\nStir in all-purpose flour and cook for about 2 minutes to make a roux.\nGradually whisk in the whole milk, heavy cream, and dry white wine.\nCook, stirring constantly, until the sauce thickens.\nRemove from heat and stir in grated Gruyère cheese, grated Parmesan cheese, chopped fresh parsley, salt, white pepper, and a pinch of cayenne pepper if desired.\n\n3. Finish the Lobsters:\nRemove the lobster meat from the shells and chop it into bite-sized pieces.\nAdd the lobster meat to the Thermidor sauce and mix well.\n\n4. Prepare the Topping:\nIn a small bowl, combine fresh bread crumbs, melted unsalted butter, and grated Parmesan cheese.\n\n5. Broil the Lobster Thermidor:\nPreheat your oven’s broiler.\nSpoon the lobster mixture back into the lobster shells.\nSprinkle the breadcrumb topping over each lobster half.\nPlace the lobsters under the broiler for 2-3 minutes or until the topping is golden and bubbly.\n\n6. Serve and Garnish:\nGarnish your Lobster Thermidor with chopped fresh parsley.\nServe immediately and savor this luxurious seafood delight!','2023-09-20 09:08:55.946074','Lobster Thermidor',13,6,'expensive','hard',120,'A Luxurious Seafood Extravaganza',0),(41,'2023-09-20 09:33:09.385507',NULL,'1. Prepare the Coffee Soaking Mixture:\nIn a shallow dish, combine brewed espresso, coffee liqueur, and granulated sugar. Stir until the sugar dissolves. Set aside to cool.\n\n2. Make the Mascarpone Filling:\nIn a mixing bowl, whisk together mascarpone cheese, powdered sugar, and vanilla extract until smooth and creamy. Set aside.\n\n3. Assemble the Tiramisu:\nQuickly dip each ladyfinger cookie into the coffee mixture, ensuring they are soaked but not soggy.\nArrange a layer of soaked ladyfingers in the bottom of a serving dish or individual dessert glasses.\n\n4. Add the Mascarpone Layer:\nSpread half of the mascarpone mixture over the ladyfingers.\n\n5. Repeat Layers:\nCreate another layer of soaked ladyfingers on top of the mascarpone mixture.\nFinish with a layer of the remaining mascarpone mixture.\n\n6. Chill:\nCover the dish or glasses with plastic wrap and refrigerate for at least 4 hours or overnight to allow the flavors to meld.\n\n7. Serve and Garnish:\nBefore serving, dust the top with unsweetened cocoa powder and garnish with dark chocolate shavings if desired.\nServe your Tiramisu chilled, and savor this classic Italian dessert!','2023-09-20 09:38:44.440334','Tiramisu',4,3,'medium','hard',30,'An Irresistible Italian Dessert',0),(42,'2023-09-20 09:47:05.109417',NULL,'1. Prepare the Dashi:\nIn a saucepan, bring the dashi to a simmer over medium heat. If you’re using dried dashi granules, follow the package instructions for dilution.\n\n2. Add Tofu and Wakame:\nOnce the dashi is simmering, add the cubed tofu and dried wakame seaweed.\nLet it simmer for about 2-3 minutes until the seaweed is rehydrated and the tofu is heated through.\n\n3. Dissolve Miso Paste:\nIn a small bowl, dissolve the miso paste in a few tablespoons of warm water to create a smooth paste.\n\n4. Add Miso Paste:\nGradually add the miso paste to the soup, stirring gently to combine.\nBe careful not to boil the soup once the miso is added to preserve its flavor.\n\n5. Add Optional Ingredients:\nIf desired, you can add sliced mushrooms, sliced carrots, or spinach leaves to the soup for added texture and flavor.\n\n6. Garnish and Serve:\nLadle the miso soup into bowls.\nGarnish with thinly sliced green onions.\nServe hot and savor this comforting Japanese classic!','2023-09-20 09:47:05.109417','Miso Soup',11,1,'cheap','easy',15,'A Comforting Japanese Classic',0),(43,'2023-09-20 11:34:18.719317',NULL,'1. Prepare the Dough:\nIn a small bowl, combine lukewarm water, sugar, and active dry yeast. Let it sit for about 5-10 minutes until frothy.\nIn a larger mixing bowl, combine flour and salt.\nGradually pour the yeast mixture and vegetable oil into the flour.\nMix until a soft dough forms.\nKnead the dough on a floured surface for about 5 minutes until smooth.\nPlace the dough back in the bowl, cover it with a cloth, and let it rest for 30 minutes to rise.\n\n2. Shape and Fry:\nAfter the dough has risen, divide it into small portions.\nRoll each portion into a thin circle or oval shape, about 1/4 inch thick.\nIn a deep frying pan, heat vegetable oil over medium-high heat until it reaches 350°F (175°C).\nCarefully slide each piece of dough into the hot oil.\nFry until both sides are golden brown and crispy, about 2-3 minutes per side.\nUse a slotted spoon to remove the lángos from the oil and place them on paper towels to drain excess oil.\n\n3. Top and Serve:\nWhile still hot, rub minced garlic over the surface of each lángos (if desired).\nGenerously spread sour cream on top.\nSprinkle with grated cheese and chopped fresh parsley.\nYou can also add other toppings like sausages, bacon, or vegetables.\n\n4. Enjoy:\nLángos is best enjoyed hot and fresh out of the fryer.\nServe and savor this Hungarian street food classic!','2023-09-20 11:46:18.579655','Lángos',12,2,'cheap','medium',60,'Hungary’s Irresistible Fried Dough Delight',0),(44,'2023-09-23 07:20:11.499498',NULL,'Step 1\nSeason chicken on both sides with 1 1/4 teaspoons salt and 1/2 teaspoon pepper. Dredge chicken in flour.\nStep 2\nIn large skillet over medium-high heat, heat butter and oil until butter is melted. Working in batches, add chicken to skillet and cook until golden brown, about 2 minutes per side. Transfer chicken to a plate.\nStep 3\nReduce heat to medium. Cook garlic, stirring frequently, until fragrant and light golden, about 1 minute. Add wine and simmer, stirring occasionally, until almost reduced, 2 to 4 minutes.\nStep 4\nAdd broth, scraping up any brown bits on bottom of pan, then slowly stir in cream. Stir in capers, 3 tablespoons lemon juice, and 2 teaspoons lemon zest; season with salt and pepper, if needed. Add gnocchi and toss to coat in sauce.\nStep 5\nBring to a boil over high heat, then reduce heat to medium-high and simmer, stirring frequently, until gnocchi is tender, 8 to 10 minutes; season with salt and pepper. Return chicken to skillet, turning to coat in sauce. Cook until chicken is warmed through, about 2 minutes more. Top with lemon rounds and parsley.','2023-09-23 07:28:16.796993','Creamy Chicken Piccata',2,1,'cheap','easy',45,'An Italian-American classic',0),(45,'2023-09-23 07:26:11.341062',NULL,'Step 1\nPreheat oven to 400°. In a large ovenproof skillet or medium baking dish, combine tomatoes, shallot, garlic, and all but 1 tablespoon oil. Season with salt and red pepper flakes and toss to combine.\nStep 2\nPlace feta into center of tomato mixture and drizzle with remaining 1 tablespoon oil. Scatter thyme sprigs over tomatoes. Bake for 40 to 45 minutes, until tomatoes are bursting and feta is golden on top.\nStep 3\nMeanwhile, in a large pot of boiling salted water, cook pasta until al dente according to package directions. Reserve ½ cup pasta water before draining.\nStep 4\nTo skillet with tomatoes and feta, add cooked pasta, reserved pasta water, and lemon zest (if using) and stir until combined. Garnish with basil. ','2023-09-23 07:26:11.341062','Baked Feta Pasta',2,1,'cheap','easy',50,'Simple, versatile, undeniably delicious',0),(46,'2023-09-23 07:35:26.906108',NULL,'Step 1\nIn a large pot of boiling salted water, cook pasta, stirring occasionally, until al dente, usually 2 to 3 minutes less than package instructions. Reserve 2 cups pasta water and drain pasta.\nStep 2\nMeanwhile, in a large, high-sided skillet over medium-high heat, heat 1 tablespoon oil. Cook sausage, breaking up with a wooden spoon, until cooked through and browned, about 8 minutes.\nStep 3\nAdd bell peppers, onion, 1/4 teaspoon salt, and remaining 2 tablespoons oil. Cook over medium-high heat, stirring occasionally, until light golden and tender, about 8 minutes. Add garlic and red pepper and cook, stirring, until fragrant, about 2 minutes more.\nStep 4\nPour 1 1/2 cups reserved pasta water into skillet, then add cream cheese, heavy cream, Parmesan, and 1/4 teaspoon salt. Bring to a boil, stirring, until cheese is melted and sauce is smooth. Add pasta and return sausage to skillet. Toss to coat, adding more pasta water a few tablespoons at a time if needed. Add spinach and stir until just wilted, about 2 minutes.\nStep 5\nDivide pasta among bowls. Top with more Parmesan.','2023-09-23 07:35:26.906108','Sausage & Peppers Shells',2,1,'medium','easy',45,'Fun and simple comfort food',0),(47,'2023-09-23 07:39:16.276765',NULL,'Step 1\nIn a large pot over medium-high heat, cook ground beef, onion, and garlic, stirring occasionally, until beef is browned, 5 to 6 minutes. Add water, tomatoes, and taco seasoning, then cover and bring to a boil.\nStep 2\nBreak spaghetti in half lengthwise and add to sauce. Reduce heat to medium, cover, and simmer until pasta is tender, 12 to 14 minutes.\nStep 3\nRemove from heat and stir in Velveeta, cheddar, and cilantro until cheese is melted. Serve topped with more cilantro and sour cream, if using.','2023-09-23 07:39:16.276765','Taco Spaghetti',2,1,'cheap','easy',40,'Because why not',0),(48,'2023-09-23 07:45:24.259570',NULL,'Step 1\nPreheat oven to 425º. Season chicken on both sides with 3/4 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper. In a large straight-sided skillet over medium-high heat, heat 1 tablespoon oil. Add chicken and cook, turning occasionally, until golden brown, 4 to 6 minutes per side. Transfer to a plate.\nStep 2\nIn same skillet over medium heat, heat remaining 1 tablespoon oil. Add onion and garlic and cook, stirring occasionally, until tender, 3 to 5 minutes. Add tomatoes and wine and cook, stirring and scraping up any brown bits on bottom of pan, until wine is mostly evaporated and tomatoes are just starting to wilt, about 2 minutes. Pour in broth and and cream and bring to a boil. Stir in gnocchi and nestle chicken back into pan.\nStep 3\nBake until chicken is cooked through and an instant-read thermometer inserted into thickest part registers 165°, 8 to 10 minutes. Transfer chicken to a cutting board.\nStep 4\nStir 2 tablespoons pesto into skillet. Top with mozzarella (if using). Continue to bake until pesto is warmed through and cheese is melted, about 4 minutes more. Let cool slightly.\nStep 5\nThinly slice chicken and return to skillet. Dollop top of bake with remaining 6 tablespoons pesto. Sprinkle with basil and pine nuts.','2023-09-23 07:45:24.259570','Creamy Chicken Skillet',2,1,'cheap','medium',65,'Melt-in-the-mouth, silky flavor',0),(49,'2023-09-23 08:56:07.603819',NULL,'Step 1\nMake chicken: In a large, deep-sided skillet over medium heat, cook bacon until crispy and fat is rendered, 4 to 5 minutes. Using a slotted spoon, transfer bacon to a plate; keep bacon fat in skillet.\nStep 2\nIn a shallow dish, whisk together flour, salt, pepper, Italian seasoning, onion powder, and garlic powder. Return skillet to medium-high heat. Lightly coat chicken cutlets in flour mixture and add to skillet. Cook, flipping halfway, until both sides are deeply golden, 4 to 6 minutes per side. Transfer chicken to a plate.\nStep 3\nMake panko topping: Return skillet to medium-low heat. Add oil, panko bread crumbs, Italian seasoning, everything bagel seasoning, salt, pepper, and red pepper flakes. Cook, stirring frequently, until panko mixture is golden, 5 to 6 minutes. Transfer to a bowl.\nStep 4\nMake sauce: Return skillet to medium heat and add oil, garlic, pepper, and red pepper flakes (if using). Cook, stirring, until garlic is golden. Add marinara, sugar, and water and bring to a simmer.\nStep 5\nAdd pasta and cook, stirring occasionally, until noodles are al dente and sauce is creamy, about 12 minutes.\nStep 6\nFold in half the mozzarella and Parmesan until melty. Slice cooked chicken on the bias into strips and place on top of pasta. Remove skillet from heat, sprinkle with remaining mozzarella and Parmesan, and cover with lid to melt cheese, about 4 minutes.\nStep 7\nGarnish with panko topping, cooked bacon, and fresh herbs.','2023-09-23 08:56:07.603819','Chicken Parmesan Pasta',2,1,'medium','medium',90,'The godness of flavors',0),(50,'2023-09-23 09:00:39.512600',NULL,'Step 1\nIn a large skillet over medium-high heat, heat 2 tablespoons oil. Add mushrooms and cook, stirring occasionally, until golden brown, about 8 minutes. Add shallot and garlic and cook, stirring occasionally, until shallot is softened, about 3 minutes more; season with salt. Transfer mushroom mixture to a medium bowl.\nStep 2\nIn same skillet over medium-high heat, heat remaining 2 tablespoons oil. Add gnocchi in an even layer and cook, undisturbed, until golden brown on the bottom, about 5 minutes. Stir and continue to cook, stirring occasionally, until gnocchi is cooked through, about 2 minutes more. Add butter and return mushrooms to skillet. Cook, stirring, until butter is melted, about 2 minutes. Stir in red pepper flakes; season with salt.\nStep 3\nDivide gnocchi mixture among plates or shallow bowls. Top with Parmesan.','2023-09-23 09:00:39.512600','Crispy Gnocchi & Mushrooms',2,1,'cheap','easy',30,'Are you in a hurry?',0),(51,'2023-09-23 09:10:17.596074',NULL,'Step 1\nIn a large skillet over medium heat, heat oil. Add garlic and cook until fragrant, 1 minute. Add anchovies and cook until fragrant, 1 minute more. Add tomatoes, olives, capers, and red pepper flakes. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and let simmer, 15 minutes.\nStep 2\nMeanwhile, in a large pot of boiling salted water, cook pasta until al dente according to package directions. Drain and add sauce, tossing until coated. Sprinkle with Parmesan.','2023-09-23 09:10:17.596074','Pasta Puttanesca',2,1,'cheap','easy',25,'Bursting with flavor and so easy to prepare',0),(52,'2023-09-23 09:16:46.030966',NULL,'Step 1\nIn a large pot of boiling salted water, cook pasta, stirring occasionally, until al dente, 2 to 3 minutes less than package instructions. Reserve 1 1/2 cups pasta water and drain pasta.\nStep 2\nMeanwhile, in a large, high-sided skillet over medium-high heat, heat tomato oil. Cook sun-dried tomatoes, garlic, and red pepper, stirring frequently, until garlic is fragrant and light golden, about 3 minutes. Add crushed tomatoes, granulated sugar, and 1/2 teaspoon salt and bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low and very gently simmer, stirring occasionally, until slightly thickened and flavors have melded, about 15 minutes.\nStep 3\nMeanwhile, in a food processor or blender, combine ricotta, lemon zest, and 1/2 teaspoon salt. With the motor running, drizzle in olive oil and process on high speed until ricotta is smooth and creamy, about 2 minutes.\nStep 4\nAdd pasta plus 1 cup reserved pasta water to skillet. Increase heat to medium high, add spinach, and cook, stirring and adding more pasta water if needed, until pasta is coated in sauce and spinach is just wilted.\nStep 5\nSpoon some ricotta mixture into bottom of bowls or a serving bowl. Top with pasta and dollop with more ricotta mixture. Sprinkle with Parmesan.','2023-09-23 09:16:46.030966','Whipped Ricotta Pasta',2,1,'cheap','easy',35,'One of the best pasta upgrades',0),(53,'2023-09-23 09:23:22.722074',NULL,'Prepare\nCut your celery and get your sea salt\nFill your glass with quality ice cubes\n\n3Gin and Tonic\nPour in your Gin and top up with Tonic\nGently stir all the ingredients together for the perfect balance.\n\n5Garnish and serve\nGarnish with the celery and sprinkle the sea salt over','2023-09-23 09:23:22.722074','Nordic Gin & Tonic',6,1,'cheap','easy',5,'The classic Gin Tonic with a Nordic twist',0),(54,'2023-09-23 13:28:57.193780',NULL,'1. Sauté Vegetables:\nIn a large pot, heat olive oil over medium heat.\nAdd chopped onion, diced carrots, chopped celery, and minced garlic.\nSauté for 5-7 minutes until the vegetables are tender.\n\n2. Add Lentils and Spices:\nStir in dried lentils, ground cumin, ground coriander, smoked paprika, dried thyme, salt, and black pepper.\nCook for 2-3 minutes to toast the spices.\n\n3. Pour in Broth and Tomatoes:\nAdd vegetable broth and diced tomatoes (with their juices) to the pot.\nBring the mixture to a boil.\n\n4. Simmer:\nReduce the heat to low, cover the pot, and let the soup simmer for 25-30 minutes, or until the lentils are tender.\n\n5. Blend (Optional):\nFor a creamier texture, you can use an immersion blender to partially blend the soup. Leave some lentils and vegetables intact for texture.\n\n6. Finish and Serve:\nSqueeze the juice of one lemon into the soup and stir.\nTaste and adjust the seasoning if needed.\nServe your Vegan Lentil Soup hot, garnished with fresh parsley.\nEnjoy this nourishing and hearty vegan soup as a comforting meal!','2023-09-23 17:00:00.000000','Vegan Lentil Soup',7,6,'cheap','easy',45,'Hearty and Nourishing Comfort Food',0),(55,'2023-09-23 13:34:25.252953',NULL,'1. Cook Quinoa:\n\nIn a saucepan, combine quinoa and water (or vegetable broth).\nBring to a boil, then reduce the heat to low, cover, and simmer for 15-20 minutes, or until the quinoa is cooked and the liquid is absorbed.\nRemove from heat and let it cool.\n2. Prepare the Dressing:\n\nIn a small bowl, whisk together extra virgin olive oil, lemon juice, minced garlic, Dijon mustard, maple syrup (if using), salt, and black pepper.\n3. Combine Salad Ingredients:\n\nIn a large mixing bowl, combine the cooked and cooled quinoa with halved cherry tomatoes, diced cucumber, diced red bell pepper, finely chopped red onion, chopped fresh parsley, chopped fresh mint leaves, sliced Kalamata olives, and chopped roasted almonds (if using).\n4. Drizzle with Dressing:\n\nPour the prepared dressing over the salad ingredients.\n5. Toss and Season:\n\nGently toss the salad until all the ingredients are well combined.\nSeason with additional salt and black pepper to taste.\n6. Chill and Serve:\n\nCover the bowl and refrigerate the Vegan Quinoa Salad for at least 30 minutes before serving to allow the flavors to meld.\nServe chilled and enjoy this fresh and nutritious salad!\nThis vibrant and flavorful quinoa salad is perfect for a light lunch or as a side dish for dinner.','2023-09-23 17:00:00.000000','Quinoa Salad',7,6,'medium','easy',30,'Fresh, Colorful, and Nutrient-Rich',0),(56,'2023-09-23 13:38:53.312795',NULL,'1. Prepare the Sauce:\nIn a small bowl, whisk together soy sauce (or tamari), hoisin sauce, rice vinegar, maple syrup (or agave nectar), cornstarch, and red pepper flakes. Set aside.\n\n2. Sauté Tofu:\nIn a large skillet or wok, heat 1 tablespoon of vegetable oil over medium-high heat.\nAdd cubed tofu and stir-fry until it becomes golden brown and crispy on all sides. Remove from the skillet and set aside.\n\n3. Stir-Fry Vegetables:\nIn the same skillet, add the remaining 1 tablespoon of vegetable oil.\nAdd minced garlic and grated ginger, and stir-fry for about 30 seconds until fragrant.\nAdd broccoli florets, red bell pepper, julienned carrot, and snap peas.\nStir-fry for 3-4 minutes until the vegetables are tender-crisp.\n\n4. Add Noodles and Tofu:\nReturn the cooked rice noodles and sautéed tofu to the skillet.\nPour the prepared sauce over the noodles and tofu.\n\n5. Toss and Heat:\nToss everything together in the skillet, ensuring the sauce coats all the ingredients.\nCook for an additional 2-3 minutes until everything is heated through.\n\n6. Garnish and Serve:\nTransfer your Vegan Stir-Fried Tofu and Vegetable Noodles to serving plates.\nGarnish with sesame seeds (if desired) and serve immediately.\nEnjoy this flavorful and satisfying vegan stir-fry with an explosion of Asian-inspired tastes!','2023-09-23 17:00:00.000000','Stir-Fried Tofu and Vegetable Noodles',7,6,'medium','medium',30,'A Burst of Asian Flavors',0),(57,'2023-09-23 13:48:15.808751',NULL,'1. Sauté Aromatics:\nIn a large pot, heat olive oil over medium heat.\nAdd chopped onion and minced garlic.\nSauté for 2-3 minutes until the onions are translucent and fragrant.\n\n2. Add Sweet Potato and Peppers:\nAdd diced sweet potato, chopped red bell pepper, and chopped yellow bell pepper to the pot.\nSauté for 5-7 minutes until the vegetables begin to soften.\n\n3. Add Beans and Tomatoes:\nStir in drained and rinsed black beans and diced tomatoes (with their juices).\nAdd chili powder, ground cumin, smoked paprika, cayenne pepper, salt, and black pepper.\nMix well to combine all the ingredients.\n\n4. Pour in Broth:\nPour vegetable broth into the pot.\nBring the mixture to a boil.\n\n5. Simmer:\nReduce the heat to low, cover the pot, and let the chili simmer for 20-25 minutes, or until the sweet potatoes are tender and the flavors meld.\n\n6. Adjust Seasoning:\nTaste the chili and adjust the seasoning if needed. You can add more chili powder or spices for extra heat.\n\n7. Serve:\nLadle your Vegan Sweet Potato and Black Bean Chili into bowls.\nGarnish with avocado slices, fresh cilantro leaves, a dollop of vegan sour cream, and lime wedges if desired.\nEnjoy this hearty and flavorful vegan chili as a comforting and satisfying meal!','2023-09-23 17:00:00.000000','Sweet Potato and Black Bean Chili',7,6,'cheap','medium',45,'Hearty and Flavorful',0),(59,'2023-09-23 14:07:13.974500',NULL,'1. Prepare the Noodles:\nCook the rice noodles according to the package instructions until they are al dente.\nDrain, rinse with cold water, and set aside.\n\n2. Make the Pad Thai Sauce:\nIn a small bowl, whisk together soy sauce (or tamari), tamarind paste, maple syrup (or agave nectar), rice vinegar, and chili flakes. Set aside.\n\n3. Sauté Tofu:\nIn a large skillet or wok, heat 1 tablespoon of vegetable oil over medium-high heat.\nAdd cubed tofu and stir-fry until it becomes golden brown and crispy.\nRemove the tofu from the skillet and set it aside.\n\n4. Sauté Veggies:\nIn the same skillet, add the remaining 1 tablespoon of vegetable oil.\nAdd minced garlic, thinly sliced red bell pepper, julienned carrot, and broccoli florets.\nStir-fry for 5-7 minutes until the vegetables are tender.\n\n5. Add Noodles and Sauce:\nReturn the cooked rice noodles to the skillet with the sautéed vegetables.\nPour the prepared Pad Thai sauce over the noodles and vegetables.\n\n6. Toss and Serve:\nToss everything together in the skillet until the noodles are well coated with the sauce and heated through.\nAdd the stir-fried tofu to the noodles and gently mix.\n\n7. Garnish:\nServe your Vegan Pad Thai hot, garnished with bean sprouts, crushed roasted peanuts, and lime wedges.\nEnjoy this delicious and authentic Vegan Pad Thai, packed with Thai flavors and textures!','2023-09-23 17:00:00.000000','Vegan Pad Thai',7,6,'medium','medium',30,'A Delicious and Flavorful Thai Noodle Dish',0),(60,'2023-09-23 14:07:40.168582',NULL,'Prepare the Pie Crust:\nIn a large mixing bowl, combine the flour and salt.\nAdd the cold, cubed butter to the flour mixture. Use a pastry cutter or your fingers to work the butter into the flour until the mixture resembles coarse crumbs.\nGradually add ice water, one tablespoon at a time, and mix until the dough just comes together. You may not need all the water.\nDivide the dough into two equal portions, shape them into discs, and wrap them in plastic wrap. Refrigerate for at least 30 minutes.\n\nPrepare the Apple Filling:\nPeel, core, and thinly slice the apples.\nIn a large mixing bowl, combine the apple slices, granulated sugar, lemon juice, flour, cinnamon, nutmeg, and salt. Toss everything together until the apples are well coated.\n\nPreheat the Oven:\nPreheat your oven to 425°F (220°C). Place a baking sheet in the oven to preheat as well. This will help ensure a crisp bottom crust.\n\nRoll Out the Pie Crust:\nOn a lightly floured surface, roll out one of the chilled dough discs into a circle that\'s about 12 inches in diameter. Carefully transfer it to a 9-inch pie dish.\n\nAdd the Apple Filling:\nFill the pie crust with the prepared apple filling, mounding it slightly in the center.\nDot the filling with small pieces of butter.\n\nRoll Out the Top Crust:\nRoll out the second chilled dough disc into a similar-sized circle.\nPlace it over the apple filling.\n\nSeal and Vent:\nTrim any excess dough hanging over the edges of the pie dish. Pinch the edges of the top and bottom crusts together to seal the pie.\nCut several small slits in the top crust to allow steam to escape.\n\nApply the Egg Wash:\nIn a small bowl, whisk together the egg and water. Brush the egg wash over the top crust for a golden finish.\n\nBake:\nPlace the pie on the preheated baking sheet in the oven.\nBake for 45-55 minutes, or until the crust is golden brown and the filling is bubbly. You may want to cover the edges with foil if they start to brown too quickly.\n\nCool and Serve:\nAllow the pie to cool on a wire rack for at least 2 hours before slicing and serving. This will help the filling set.\nEnjoy your delicious homemade \"Grandma\'s Homestyle Apple Pie\"! It\'s perfect with a scoop of vanilla ice cream or a dollop of whipped cream.','2023-09-23 14:44:30.092211','Grandma\'s apple pie',4,3,'medium','medium',165,'A timeless family favorite',0),(61,'2023-09-23 14:13:59.608163',NULL,'Preheat your oven to 350°F (175°C). Grease and flour two 9-inch round cake pans.\n\nIn a large mixing bowl, whisk together the flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg, and ginger.\nIn a separate bowl, combine the vegetable oil, eggs, and vanilla extract. Mix well.\nPour the wet ingredients into the dry ingredients and stir until just combined.\nFold in the grated carrots, crushed pineapple, and chopped nuts or shredded coconut if using.\n\nDivide the batter evenly between the prepared cake pans.\nBake in the preheated oven for 25-30 minutes or until a toothpick inserted into the center of the cakes comes out clean.\nRemove the cakes from the oven and allow them to cool in the pans for 10 minutes, then transfer them to a wire rack to cool completely.\n\nIn a mixing bowl, beat the softened cream cheese and butter until smooth and creamy.\nGradually add the powdered sugar and vanilla extract, continuing to beat until the frosting is light and fluffy.\n\nOnce the cakes have cooled completely, spread a layer of cream cheese frosting on top of one of the cakes.\nPlace the second cake on top and frost the top and sides of the entire cake.\nOptional: Garnish the cake with additional chopped nuts or shredded coconut.\n\nSlice and serve your delicious homemade carrot cake. Enjoy!\nThis irresistible homemade carrot cake is sure to be a hit at any gathering or celebration.','2023-09-23 14:13:59.608163','Carrot Cake',4,3,'medium','easy',30,'Fresh, Colorful, and Nutrient-Rich',0),(62,'2023-09-23 14:15:15.356164',NULL,'1. Prepare the Miso Glaze:\nIn a small saucepan, combine white miso paste, mirin, sake, sugar, and soy sauce.\nHeat over low heat, stirring constantly until the mixture is smooth and slightly thickened.\nRemove from heat and set aside.\n\n2. Season and Sear the Wagyu Steaks:\nSeason the Wagyu steaks generously with salt and black pepper on both sides.\nIn a hot skillet or grill pan, sear the steaks for about 2-3 minutes per side for medium-rare, or adjust cooking time to your preferred doneness.\nRemove the steaks from the heat and let them rest for a few minutes.\n\n3. Prepare the Vegetables:\nWhile the steaks are resting, drizzle fresh seasonal vegetables with truffle oil and grill or roast them until tender.\n\n4. Glaze the Steaks:\nBrush the seared Wagyu steaks with the prepared miso glaze on both sides.\nPlace them under a broiler or use a culinary torch to lightly caramelize the glaze until it\'s golden brown and bubbling.\n\n5. Add Truffle Butter:\nWhile the glaze is still hot, place a tablespoon of truffle butter on each steak.\nAllow the butter to melt and infuse the steak with its rich flavor.\n\n6. Plate and Garnish:\nArrange the grilled vegetables on serving plates.\nPlace the Wagyu steaks on top of the vegetables.\nGarnish with fresh thyme sprigs and truffle shavings (if desired).\n\n7. Serve and Enjoy:\nServe your Japanese Wagyu Beef Steak with Truffle Butter and Miso Glaze immediately, accompanied by your favorite fine wine.\nThis extravagant dish combines the melt-in-your-mouth tenderness of Japanese Wagyu beef with the earthy richness of truffle and the umami depth of miso glaze, creating a culinary masterpiece that\'s worth the investment of time and resources for a special occasion.','2023-09-25 14:52:29.515487','Japanese Wagyu Beef with Truffle & Miso Glaze',11,6,'expensive','hard',120,'A Culinary Masterpiece with Wagyu, Truffle, and Miso',0),(63,'2023-09-23 14:21:20.701179',NULL,'1. Prepare the Saffron Risotto:\nIn a small bowl, soak saffron threads in 2 tablespoons of hot water for about 10 minutes.\nIn a separate saucepan, heat the vegetable broth until simmering, then reduce the heat to keep it warm.\nIn a large skillet, melt 1 tablespoon of vegan butter over medium heat.\nAdd chopped onion and minced garlic, and sauté until translucent.\nStir in Arborio rice and cook for 1-2 minutes until the rice is lightly toasted.\nPour in the dry white wine and cook until it\'s mostly absorbed.\nBegin adding the warm saffron-infused vegetable broth, one ladle at a time, stirring continuously.\nContinue adding broth and stirring until the risotto is creamy and the rice is cooked but slightly al dente (around 18-20 minutes).\nStir in the remaining 1 tablespoon of vegan butter, vegan Parmesan cheese (if using), and season with salt and white pepper. Set aside, keeping it warm.\n\n2. Prepare the Asparagus Bundles:\nPreheat your oven to 375°F (190°C).\nTrim the tough ends of the asparagus.\nBundle 3 asparagus spears together and wrap each bundle with a strip of kitchen twine.\nPlace the bundles on a baking sheet, drizzle with olive oil, and season with salt and black pepper.\nRoast in the preheated oven for 10-12 minutes or until the asparagus is tender but still crisp.\n\n3. Sear the Chilean Sea Bass:\nSeason the Chilean sea bass fillets with salt and white pepper.\nIn a large skillet, heat olive oil over medium-high heat.\nAdd the sea bass fillets, skin-side down, and sear for 4-5 minutes until the skin is crispy and the fish releases easily from the pan.\nCarefully flip the fillets and sear for an additional 3-4 minutes on the other side until the fish is opaque and flakes easily with a fork.\n\n4. Plate and Serve:\nSpoon a generous portion of saffron risotto onto each serving plate.\nPlace a Chilean sea bass fillet on top of the risotto.\nArrange the roasted asparagus bundles alongside.\nGarnish with lemon slices and fresh parsley leaves.\n\n5. Enjoy the Gastronomic Delight:\nServe the Pan-Seared Chilean Sea Bass with Saffron Risotto immediately, paired with a crisp white wine, and savor the luxurious flavors.\nThis exquisite dish combines the buttery tenderness of Chilean sea bass with the aromatic saffron-infused risotto and perfectly roasted asparagus bundles, making it a gourmet masterpiece perfect for special occasions or indulgent dinners.','2023-09-23 17:00:00.000000','Pan-Seared Chilean Sea Bass with Saffron Risotto',13,6,'expensive','hard',90,'Luxurious Sea Bass and Saffron-Infused Risotto',0),(64,'2023-09-23 14:25:37.016110',NULL,'1. Prepare the Sushi Rice:\nRinse sushi rice in cold water until the water runs clear.\nCombine rinsed rice and water in a rice cooker or saucepan. Cook according to the rice cooker\'s instructions or bring to a boil, then reduce heat to low, cover, and simmer for 18-20 minutes.\nIn a small saucepan, heat rice vinegar, sugar, and salt over low heat until the sugar and salt dissolve.\nTransfer cooked rice to a large wooden or glass bowl. Gradually pour the vinegar mixture over the rice while gently folding it in. Allow the rice to cool to room temperature.\n\n2. Prepare Sushi Fillings:\nSlice fresh sushi-grade fish into thin strips.\nCut vegetables into matchsticks or thin slices.\n\n3. Assemble Sushi Rolls:\nPlace a bamboo sushi rolling mat (makisu) on a clean surface.\nLay a sheet of plastic wrap over the mat.\nLay a sheet of nori, shiny side down, on the plastic wrap.\nWet your hands to prevent sticking, and spread a thin layer of sushi rice over the nori, leaving a 1-inch border at the top.\nArrange your desired fillings on the rice.\nCarefully lift the edge of the mat and nori, and roll it tightly over the fillings.\nUse a bit of water to seal the edge of the nori.\nSlice the roll into bite-sized pieces using a sharp, wet knife.\n\n4. Prepare Temaki Rolls:\nPlace a sheet of nori on a clean, dry surface.\nWet your hands and grab a small amount of sushi rice. Spread it diagonally across the nori sheet.\nAdd your desired fillings diagonally on top of the rice.\nFold the bottom corner of the nori over the fillings and roll it into a cone shape.\nUse a bit of water to seal the edge.\n\n5. Serve:\nServe your homemade sushi and temaki rolls with soy sauce, wasabi, and pickled ginger.\n\n6. Enjoy the Japanese Culinary Experience:\nSavor the flavors and textures of your homemade sushi and temaki rolls, and share this delightful meal with friends and family.\nMaking sushi and temaki at home allows you to customize your rolls with your favorite ingredients and enjoy the art of Japanese cuisine in the comfort of your own kitchen.','2023-09-23 17:00:00.000000','Homemade Sushi and Temaki Rolls',11,6,'expensive','medium',120,'Savor the Art of Japanese Cuisine in the Comfort of Your Home',0),(65,'2023-09-23 14:25:41.947967',NULL,'Preheat your oven to 350°F (175°C). Line a muffin tin with paper liners or grease it well.\n\nIn a large mixing bowl, whisk together the flour, granulated sugar, brown sugar, cocoa powder, baking powder, baking soda, and salt.\nIn a separate bowl, whisk together the melted butter, eggs, buttermilk, and vanilla extract until well combined.\nPour the wet ingredients into the dry ingredients and stir until just combined.\nGently fold in the chocolate chips.\n\nDivide the muffin batter evenly among the prepared muffin cups, filling each about two-thirds full.\n\nBake in the preheated oven for 18-20 minutes or until a toothpick inserted into the center of a muffin comes out clean or with a few moist crumbs (avoid hitting a chocolate chip).\n\nAllow the muffins to cool in the pan for 5 minutes, then transfer them to a wire rack to cool completely.\n\nEnjoy your ultimate chocolate chip muffins for breakfast, as a snack, or any time you crave a chocolatey treat!','2023-09-23 14:33:54.826037','Chocolate Chip Muffin',4,3,'cheap','easy',30,'Small bites, big delights',0),(66,'2023-09-23 14:33:01.039707',NULL,'In a mixing bowl, combine the chia seeds, coconut milk, honey or maple syrup, and vanilla extract.\nWhisk everything together until well combined.\nCover the bowl and refrigerate it for at least 2 hours or overnight. Stir the mixture after the first 15 minutes to prevent clumping, and then again before leaving it to set.\n\nIn a separate bowl, combine the fresh pineapple chunks and 2 tablespoons of honey or maple syrup.\nGently toss the pineapple in the sweet syrup until well coated.\nRefrigerate until you\'re ready to assemble the chia pudding.\n\nWhen the chia pudding has thickened to your liking (after at least 2 hours), give it a good stir.\nSpoon the chia pudding into serving glasses or bowls.\nTop each serving with the sweetened pineapple chunks.\n\nServe your tropical chia pudding with pineapple for a refreshing and nutritious breakfast, snack, or dessert.','2023-09-23 14:33:01.039707','Chia Pudding',4,3,'cheap','easy',15,'Tropical delight with pineapple',0),(67,'2023-09-23 14:33:37.501507',NULL,'1. Prepare the Marinade:\n\nIn a bowl, combine grated pear, minced garlic, soy sauce, sugar, honey, mirin, sesame oil, grated ginger, and black pepper to create the bulgogi marinade.\n\n2. Marinate the Beef:\nPlace the thinly sliced beef in a large resealable plastic bag or a bowl.\nAdd the sliced onions to the beef.\nPour the bulgogi marinade over the beef and onions.\nSeal the bag or cover the bowl and marinate in the refrigerator for at least 1 hour, but ideally 2 hours, to allow the flavors to meld.\n\n3. Cook the Bulgogi:\nHeat a grill pan or a skillet over medium-high heat.\nAdd a bit of vegetable oil to prevent sticking.\nCook the marinated beef and onions in batches for 2-3 minutes per batch until the beef is cooked through and has a nice caramelized color.\n\n4. Garnish and Serve:\nArrange the cooked bulgogi on a platter.\nGarnish with sliced green onions and sesame seeds.\n\n5. Serve Korean Bulgogi:\nServe your Korean Bulgogi Beef with steamed white rice and lettuce leaves for wrapping.\nOptionally, provide ssamjang (Korean dipping sauce) for extra flavor.\n\n6. Enjoy Korean Culinary Delight:\nWrap a slice of bulgogi in a lettuce leaf, add a dollop of ssamjang if desired, and savor the explosion of flavors in this classic Korean dish.\nKorean Bulgogi Beef is a beloved Korean barbecue dish known for its sweet and savory flavors. It\'s a delightful and interactive dining experience perfect for sharing with family and friends.','2023-09-23 17:00:00.000000','Korean Bulgogi Beef',11,6,'medium','medium',120,'A Flavorful Journey Through Korean Cuisine',0),(68,'2023-09-23 14:38:26.623214',NULL,'1. Prepare the Green Curry Paste:\nIn a food processor, combine green Thai chilies, garlic, shallot, lemongrass, ginger, galangal, lime zest, ground coriander, ground cumin, ground white pepper, and ground turmeric.\nBlend until a smooth paste forms, adding vegetable oil as needed to facilitate blending. Set aside.\n\n2. Prepare the Curry:\nIn a large skillet or wok, heat a bit of coconut milk over medium heat until it begins to simmer.\nAdd 2 tablespoons of the green curry paste and stir-fry for 1-2 minutes until fragrant.\n\n3. Add Tofu and Veggies:\nAdd cubed tofu, sliced red bell pepper, green bell pepper, zucchini, bamboo shoots, and snap peas to the skillet.\nStir-fry for 2-3 minutes to coat the ingredients with the curry paste.\n\n4. Pour in Coconut Milk:\nPour the remaining coconut milk into the skillet.\nStir in soy sauce and brown sugar.\n\n5. Simmer:\nReduce heat to low and let the curry simmer for 10-15 minutes, allowing the flavors to meld and the vegetables to become tender.\n\n6. Taste and Adjust:\nTaste the curry and adjust the seasoning by adding more soy sauce or brown sugar if needed.\n\n7. Serve:\nServe your Thai Green Curry with Tofu over cooked jasmine rice.\nGarnish with fresh Thai basil leaves.\n\n8. Enjoy the Fragrant Thai Delight:\nEnjoy the vibrant and fragrant flavors of this Thai green curry, a comforting and satisfying dish.\nThai Green Curry with Tofu is a popular Thai dish known for its aromatic herbs and creamy coconut milk. It\'s a delightful combination of sweet, savory, and spicy flavors that makes for a memorable meal.','2023-09-23 17:00:00.000000','Thai Green Curry with Tofu',11,6,'expensive','medium',45,'A Vibrant and Fragrant Thai Delight',0),(69,'2023-09-23 14:42:29.311543',NULL,'Preheat your oven to 350°F (175°C). Grease a 4x8-inch (or similar size) loaf pan.\n\nIn a mixing bowl, mash the ripe bananas with a fork until smooth.\n\nStir the melted butter into the mashed bananas.\n\nAdd the baking soda and a pinch of salt to the banana-butter mixture and stir until well combined. Let it sit for 1-2 minutes; it will start to bubble.\n\nStir in the granulated sugar, beaten egg, and vanilla extract until the mixture is smooth.\n\nGently fold in the all-purpose flour until just incorporated. Be careful not to overmix; it\'s okay if there are a few lumps.\n\nIf you\'re using any optional mix-ins, such as chopped nuts or chocolate chips, fold them into the batter at this point.\n\nPour the banana bread batter into the greased loaf pan.\n\nBake in the preheated oven for 60-65 minutes or until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean. If the top starts to brown too quickly, you can loosely cover it with aluminum foil.\n\nAllow the banana bread to cool in the pan for about 10 minutes, then remove it from the pan and transfer it to a wire rack to cool completely.\n\nSlice your classic banana bread and savor each moist and flavorful bite.\nThis classic banana bread recipe is perfect for using up overripe bananas and makes a delightful treat for breakfast or snacking.','2023-09-23 14:42:29.311543','Classic Banana Bread',4,3,'medium','easy',65,'Turn overripe bananas into blissful bites',0),(70,'2023-09-23 14:59:38.300247',NULL,'Heat the vegetable oil in a large soup pot over medium-high heat.\nAdd the cubed beef and sear until it\'s browned on all sides. Remove the beef and set it aside.\n\nIn the same pot, add the finely chopped onions and minced garlic. Sauté until the onions become translucent.\n\nStir in the Hungarian paprika, caraway seeds, salt, black pepper, marjoram, and thyme (if using). Cook for a minute or two until the spices become fragrant.\n\nReturn the seared beef to the pot and add the beef broth and bay leaves. Bring to a boil, then reduce the heat and let it simmer, covered, for about 1 hour.\n\nAdd the diced potatoes, sliced carrots, chopped green and red bell peppers, canned diced tomatoes (with juice), and tomato paste to the pot. Add 1 cup of water as needed to ensure the ingredients are well-covered.\n\nContinue simmering, covered, for another 45 minutes to 1 hour, or until the beef is tender, and the vegetables are cooked through.\n\nRemove the bay leaves before serving.\nLadle the Authentic Hungarian Goulash Soup into bowls.\nGarnish each serving with a dollop of sour cream and a sprinkle of fresh parsley.\n\nEnjoy this authentic taste of Hungarian cuisine!','2023-09-23 14:59:38.300247','Hungarian Goulash Soup',3,3,'medium','medium',120,'A flavorful fusion of tradition and comfort',0),(71,'2023-09-23 15:04:07.565159',NULL,'In a large soup pot, heat the olive oil over medium heat.\nAdd the finely chopped onion and minced garlic. Sauté until the onions become translucent.\n\nStir in the diced carrots, celery, zucchini, and yellow squash. Sauté for about 5 minutes until the vegetables start to soften.\nAdd Green Beans, Tomatoes, and Broth:\n\nAdd the green beans, canned diced tomatoes (with juice), and vegetable broth to the pot. Stir well.\n\nBring the mixture to a boil, then reduce the heat to low, cover, and simmer for about 10-15 minutes, or until the vegetables are tender.\n\nStir in the kidney beans, cannellini beans, and small pasta.\nContinue simmering for an additional 10-12 minutes, or until the pasta is cooked al dente.\n\nSeason the soup with dried Italian seasoning, salt, and black pepper to taste.\n\nLadle the Classic Minestrone Soup into bowls.\nGarnish each serving with fresh chopped basil leaves and grated Parmesan cheese if desired.\n\nSavor the robust flavors of this classic Italian Minestrone Soup, a nourishing and satisfying meal.\nThis recipe brings you the comforting flavors of traditional Italian minestrone soup, filled with a variety of vegetables, beans, and pasta in a flavorful broth.','2023-09-23 15:04:07.565159','Minestrone Soup',3,3,'medium','easy',45,'A hearty and nutrient-packed italian speciality',0),(72,'2023-09-23 15:07:05.130127',NULL,'In a large soup pot, melt the butter over medium heat.\nAdd the chopped onion and minced garlic. Sauté until the onions become translucent and fragrant, about 3-4 minutes.\n\nStir in the frozen green peas and continue to cook for another 2-3 minutes, allowing the peas to thaw slightly.\n\nPour in the vegetable broth, covering the peas and onions. Bring the mixture to a gentle boil.\n\nReduce the heat to low and let the soup simmer for about 15-20 minutes, or until the peas are tender.\n\nUsing an immersion blender or a countertop blender (in batches), carefully blend the soup until smooth and creamy.\n\nReturn the blended soup to the pot.\n\nStir in the heavy cream and warm the soup over low heat. Do not boil after adding the cream.\n\nSeason the soup with salt and black pepper to taste. Adjust the seasonings if needed.\n\nLadle the Creamy Pea Soup into bowls.\nGarnish each serving with fresh mint leaves for a burst of flavor and color.\nServe with croutons or crusty bread if desired.\n\nRelish the velvety texture and fresh taste of this Creamy Pea Soup as a comforting starter or a light meal.\nThis simple and elegant recipe transforms ordinary frozen peas into a delightful, vibrant green soup that\'s perfect for any occasion.','2023-09-23 15:07:05.130127','Creamy Pea Soup',3,3,'cheap','easy',45,'Fresh and green',0),(73,'2023-09-23 15:38:13.061446',NULL,'In a large pot, add the chicken or vegetable broth, minced garlic, sliced ginger, soy sauce, miso paste (if using), and sesame oil.\nBring the mixture to a simmer over medium heat.\nLet it simmer for about 15-20 minutes, allowing the flavors to meld together.\nTaste the broth and adjust the seasoning with salt and pepper if needed.\n\nWhile the broth is simmering, cook the ramen noodles according to the package instructions.\nDrain and set aside.\n\nIn a separate pan, sauté the sliced mushrooms in a bit of oil until they are tender and browned. Set them aside.\nIn the same pan, you can quickly blanch the baby spinach or bok choy leaves until they wilt. Remove and set them aside.\nSlice the boiled eggs in half.\n\nDivide the cooked ramen noodles among serving bowls.\nLadle the hot broth over the noodles, making sure to include some minced garlic and ginger in each bowl.\nArrange the sautéed mushrooms, bamboo shoots, green onions, and egg halves on top of the noodles.\nAdd the wilted spinach or bok choy.\nGarnish with nori seaweed sheets and sesame seeds, if desired.\n\nServe the ramen hot and enjoy!','2023-09-23 15:38:13.061446','Ramen Soup',3,3,'expensive','hard',60,'Inspired by traditional Japanese ramen',0),(74,'2023-09-23 15:41:24.310768',NULL,'In a blender or food processor, combine the chopped tomatoes, cucumber, red bell pepper, red onion, and minced garlic. Pulse until the mixture is finely chopped but still slightly chunky.\n\nTransfer the mixture to a large bowl and add the tomato juice, red wine vinegar, and extra-virgin olive oil. Stir well to combine.\n\nSeason the gazpacho with salt and black pepper to taste. Keep in mind that gazpacho is best served chilled, so you may want to make it slightly more seasoned than you would prefer, as flavors can mellow when it\'s cold.\n\nCover the bowl and refrigerate the gazpacho for at least 2 hours to allow the flavors to meld and for it to become nicely chilled.\n\nBefore serving, taste the gazpacho again and adjust the seasoning if necessary.\n\nLadle the chilled gazpacho into bowls, garnish with fresh basil or cilantro leaves if desired, and enjoy this refreshing Spanish tomato soup on a hot day..','2023-09-23 15:41:24.310768','Refreshing Gazpacho',3,3,'cheap','easy',30,'The chilled spanish tomato soup',0);
